.TH "hash_at_level" 9 "hash_at_level" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hash_at_level \- compute the location of the block's hash at the given level
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" hash_at_level
.BI "(const struct merkle_tree_params *params "  ","
.BI "pgoff_t dindex "  ","
.BI "unsigned int level "  ","
.BI "pgoff_t *hindex "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *hoffset "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "params" 12
(in) the Merkle tree parameters
.IP "dindex" 12
(in) the index of the data block being verified
.IP "level" 12
(in) the level of hash we want (0 is leaf level)
.IP "hindex" 12
(out) the index of the hash block containing the wanted hash
.IP "hoffset" 12
(out) the byte offset to the wanted hash within the hash block
